inglise keeles	The course is designed for master level students who lack systematic knowledge of the basics of quantitative data analysis or the relevant practical skills or who wish to brush up on or systematise such knowledge or skills. The course also gives introductory knowledge and skills for using R, however, the main focus of the course is on learning the analysis methods (for a more thorough handling of R, see SVUH.00.149 Statistical Software R for the Social Sciences).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give an overview of main quantitative data analysis methods at the beginner's level that can be applied to measure and understand various processes in the society and organizations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student: - knows the beginner's level analysis methods for quantitative data, and is able to apply them to solve practical exercises; - knows the basics of inferential data analysis and is able to put them into practice and interpret the results adequately; - is familiar with the principles of R and can use R for solving simpler tasks.
